[{"id":"FT578016","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"The figure presents the sphere at point Z. Four rays are drawn from point Z. Ray 2 points along the string, upward and to the left. Ray 1 points upward and to the right, perpendicular to the string. Ray 3 points downward and to the left, opposite of ray 1, and perpendicular to ray 2. Ray 4 points vertically downward from point Z. \" height=\"167\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/8416d1fb3001762f177cd418ffdcfa7e/original.png\" width=\"188\" /></p>\n\n<p>Four directions at point Z are indicated as I, II, III, and IV in the figure above. Which of the arrows best indicates the direction of the acceleration of the sphere at point Z?</p>\n","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"The figure presents a sphere attached to the end of a string that extends upward and to the right. Three points are indicated along the path of the sphere, which is a segment of a circle . Point X is indicated where the sphere is currently positioned, at the left end point of the path. Point Y is indicated at the lowest point of the path. Point Z is indicated at the right end point of the path, directly to the right of Point X. \" height=\"180\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/4e232a81-4cc3-4e1d-83b8-3d83ea1bc4a9.png\" width=\"300\" /></p>\n\n<p>A sphere on the end of a string is released from rest at point X and swings through point Y to point Z, as shown in the figure above. Point Y is the lowest point for the sphere as it swings. Air resistance is negligible.</p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p>I</p>","<p>II</p>","<p>III</p>","<p>IV</p>","<p>The direction of the acceleration is undefined because the acceleration equals zero.</p>"],"answer":1}]